Adverb
An adverb is a word that modifies any of:
  verb,
  adjective,
  determiner,
  clause,
  preposition,
or sentence.

Adverbs typically express any of:
  manner,
  place,
  time,
  frequency,
  degree,
or level of certainty.

They typically answer any of the questions:
  how?,
  in what way?,
  when?,
  where?,
and to what extent?.
